Team changes
------------

This release includes contributions from John Lockhart who has recently joined
the Errata Tool team as a developer (while still spending part of his time
looking after TPS, OATS and Stable Systems).

Note also that the RPMDiff enhancements included in this release and the
previous release were contributed by the
[RPMDiff team](https://docs.engineering.redhat.com/display/HTD/RPMDiff).


What's Next
------------

### Errata Tool 3.13

3.12.5 is the final major release in the Errata Tool 3.12 release period. Any
remaining bugs and RFEs flagged for errata-3.12 will soon be moved to
errata-3.13. Once enough content is verified and ready to ship we will prepare
the next release. The next release will be 3.13.0.

To see current work in progress take a look at the [scrum board in
JIRA][scrumboard].

To see what's currently scheduled for ET 3.13 take a look at [bugs flagged with
errata-3.13 in Bugzilla][bugs_this] or the [Errata Tool Road Map][roadmap].

### Errata Tool 3.14

The planning and backlog for Errata Tool is managed in Bugzilla. For more details
see [here][schedulingfaq].

To see what's currently scheduled for Errata Tool 3.14 take a look at [bugs
flagged with errata-3.14][bugs_next].

